%C A394887 The values that A051903 (and also A007814) obtains for the 17 initial terms are: 0, 1, 2, 5, 8, 9, 11, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, 18, 19, 20, 21, 24.
%C A394887 If it exists, a(18) > 2^32.
%e A394887 Let x = A276086(a(17)) = A276086(1258291200) = 32470244413303490673777468789898714556998166594933197461202886423699943691 = 7^6 * 11^8 * 13 * 17^13 * 19^13 * 23^14 * 29^5. A099307(x) = 22, so x is in A099308, thus 1258291200 is in A328116, and it is also the first value in that sequence with the maximal exponent (A051903) = 24, which is larger than the previous record, which was 21.
%o A394887 (PARI)
%o A394887 \\ Uses also the code given in A394886:
%o A394887 m=-1; k=0; for(n=1,2^35,if(!(n%(2^25)),print1("("n")")); e=A051903(n); if(e>m && is_A328116(n), m=e; k++; write("b394887.txt", k, " ", n); print1(n,"(",m,"), ")));
